C. Lester Hogan, president and chief executive officer of the Fairchild Camera and In strument Corporation, told stockholders at yesterday's an nnual meeting at Palo Alto, Calif., that the rebuilding of the company would be com pleted by midyear.

“By July,” he said, “our ex pansion and modernization program [in the semiconductor division] will be essentially completed. With this phase be hind us, Fairchild can success fully lock horns at any level of competition with the very best in the industry.”

Mr. Hogan said management was “closely watching” the business picture and attempting to offset any unfavorable econ omic influences through “more closely controlled expenditures, increased penetration of foreign markets and an aggressive do mestic sales program.”

Stockholders re‐elected eight directors and approved selec tion of auditors.